args: Here you are: a nice slice of berry pie\nto beat that midday sugar crash.
HECK yeah. This looks delish! I'll help\nmyself to Farren's portion while I'm at it.
Guy's got no time to spare right now.\nHe's runnin' all over the place meddling,\nexcept, y'know. Helpfully.
And since he's tied up, that means it's cool\nfor me to take the whole pie for myself,\nright? Right!
No. We're saving a piece to give\nFarren later.
And so you have arrived, Lil' Barb.\nWhat shall we play today? Cards? Dice?
Cards! I owe you for yesterday!
Heh heh. Bluster all you want, but you may\nwell find yourself in trouble again today.\nYou sure you're up for it?

A needless question.
It's not a matter of winning or losing.
We're here for the thrill.
...Right, pal?
Yeah, I hear ya! But either way,\nI'M bringin' home the bacon today!\nFiguratively. ...I'm gonna win.
I'm baaack! Oh man, this Halidom place is\nthe BEST. The food's to die for, and there's\nall sortsa shenanigans I can get up to.
It's like night and day from those\nmiserable days we spent with the\nSyndicate. Don't ya agree, Farren?!
Day in, day out, from sunup to sundown,\nhe's out there doin' stuff for other people.
Why? We're finally free from the\nSyndicate. The kid oughta be goofin'\noff and doin' whatever he wants...
A few days later, in the middle of a fiend hunt...
Hrk! Be careful, everyone.\nThis fiend is strong!
It'll be dangerous to try'n take it head on.\nWe should skirt around and strike from the\nback. That oughta bring 'er down quick.
Easier said than done. Doesn't seem\nlike we got any chance TO get behind it!
Then we just gotta MAKE an opening.\nI'll go get its attention.
But that'll put you in danger!
If anyone's gonna be bait, it should be me.\nThis body of mine's sturdier than a normal\nperson's.
Come on, don't worry about me. I was a\nmerc—got real used to doin' this sorta\nthing in those days.

Fightin' comes about as easily to me as
wipin' my backside. I know all the tricks—
not necessarily to win, but to get outta
any sorta scrap alive.
It IS dangerous, but I trust you, Ranzal.
That's what I like to hear. Now c'mon—\ny'all separate out from me and watch\nfor a chance to make your move!
Oh YEAH! Time to DO this! HRAAAH!
All righty... Heh. If I focus on my defense,\nattacks like these won't—
Whoa there! This thing's a little scrappier\nthan I was thinkin' it'd be.
Idiot! You're supposed to let\nME take the hits here!
Farren! Lil' Barb! You guys okay?!
Owww... Er, yeah! No sweat!\nLike I told you, I'm tough.
Now, come at me, fiends!\nGive me your best shot!

I don't know what kinda idiotic pride
thing you're tryin' to do, but quit gettin'
knocked around and let MY part of the
body take the hits, Farren!
Phew... We managed. Farren,\nare you sure you're really okay?
I see. Good. Nevertheless... I have to say\nthat what you did back there scared me.
Er, sorry about that! My body just kind of\nmoved on its own when I realized that\nRanzal was in danger.

I'm grateful for you helpin' me out
there, but seriously, you're bein' way
too reckless. You've only got one life
to lose, y'know.
But...that's the only way I'm able to be of\nany use to anybody...
Anyway, I promise I'm okay!\nSee? No big injuries or anything.
Did you deliberately take that hit from the\nfiend on the human side of your body?
Oh, uh...yeah. If I had taken it from the\nright side, it might've hurt you, so—
Look, kid. I was MADE to be a shell. I'm\ntough. Tougher than you, at the very least.
So just...don't do that kinda stuff.\nLet me soak the damage. You feel me?
Oh, sorry! I just...never would've thought\nthat you worried about me like that.
Don't BS me, kid! I've had it up to here\nfightin' with someone who won't actually\ntrust in me!
Wait, no, it's not that I don't trust you—

Like hell it ain't. You're tryin' to do
everything on your own. You're reachin'
for cookies on the top shelf, and you ain't
as tall as you think you are.
And there's nothin' I hate MORE than\nbeing underestimated, dammit!

What he said. You can't be surprised if
the folks around you start doubtin' your
faith in them when you go around
sacrificing yourself willy-nilly.
Yes. You can rely on us more.
I... Yeah. Yeah, you're right.\nI'm sorry, Lil' Barb.
Good, so you get it now?\nThere ain't gonna be a next time.
(Can't say he has me convinced.\nThis IS Farren we're talkin' about.)
